HEADWORD: Scombroid
<hw>Scom"broid</hw> <pr>(sk⟦ocr⟧m"broid)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Scomber</ets> + <ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Like or pertaining to the Mackerel family.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>Any fish of the family <fam>Scombridae</fam>,
of which the mackerel (<gen>Scomber</gen>) is the type, and including
the tuna (<gen>Thunnus</gen> and related genera).</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

